  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where is good apartment near Deloitte Chicago?",
  "response": "Finding a good apartment near Deloitte's Chicago office can be influenced by various factors such as budget, amenities, and lifestyle preferences. The Deloitte office is located in the Loop area, which is Chicago's commercial hub. Several neighborhoods around the Loop offer convenient access and various living experiences. Here are a few neighborhoods to consider:\n\n1. **The Loop**:\n   - Proximity: Closest to Deloitte\u2019s office.\n   - Lifestyle: Bustling, urban environment with easy access to public transportation.\n   - Amenities: High-rise buildings, luxury apartments, and numerous dining and entertainment options.\n\n2. **River North**:\n   - Proximity: Just north of the Loop, within walking distance or a short commute.\n   - Lifestyle: Trendy neighborhood known for its nightlife, art galleries, and upscale dining.\n   - Amenities: Stylish lofts, modern high-rises, and various amenities.\n\n3. **West Loop**:\n   - Proximity: West of the Loop, easily accessible via public transportation.\n   - Lifestyle: Rapidly growing neighborhood, popular among professionals with lots of new developments.\n   - Amenities: Industrial-style apartments, chic restaurants, and close proximity to Union Station.\n\n4. **Streeterville**:\n   - Proximity: Northeast of the Loop, around a 15-20 minute walk or quick drive.\n   - Lifestyle: Residential area with a quieter atmosphere compared to the Loop.\n   - Amenities: Luxury high-rises, beautiful lakefront views, and easy access to Navy Pier and the Magnificent Mile.\n\n5. **South Loop**:\n   - Proximity: Directly south of the Loop, easily accessible by public transportation.\n   - Lifestyle: Mix of historic buildings and modern developments, offering a more relaxed environment.\n   - Amenities: Mid-rise apartments, museums, parks, and good value for money.\n\nWhen searching for an apartment, consider using websites or apps like Zillow, Apartments.com, or Rent.com to view listings and get an idea of prices and amenities. Additionally, engaging a local real estate agent can provide personalized assistance based on your specific needs and preferences.\n\nUltimately, choosing the right neighborhood will depend on your work-life balance, commuting preferences, and desired lifestyle.",
